(* README *)

1 - Description
    -----------

    T001 provides a mechanized proof of the “Carryless Pairing” construction in 
    Rocq. The development relies on the standard libraries Arith, List, Bool,
    and PeanoNat.

    `T001__Comprehension.v` packages the core definitions, the abstract
    correctness theorem, and the concrete `P0` realizations into one
    audit-facing synopsis layer.

    `T001__Extraction_Interface.v` exposes the root-level OCaml extraction
    surface for the concrete `P0` realization and the core carryless pairing
    operations.

    The `appendix/` directory contains the proof-erasure outputs generated from
    the development.


2 - Repository Tree
    ---------------

    .
    ├── README
    │
    │      (This file.)
    │
    ├── T001__Comprehension.v
    │
    │      Audit/comprehension layer for the carryless pairing package.
    │
    ├── T001__Extraction_Interface.v
    │
    │      Root extraction interface exposing the executable `P0` pairing
    │      surface and the OCaml export directives.
    │
    ├── R01__Carryless_Pairing_Definitions.v
    │
    │      Core definitions of the carryless pairing function, including the
    │      arithmetic encoding, auxiliary constructions, and structural lemmas.
    │
    ├── R02__Carryless_Pairing_Correctness.v
    │
    │      Main correctness results. In particular, it proves 
    │      [ unpair (pair x y) = (x, y) ] under the stated Zeckendorf
    │      specification, together with supporting soundness and representation
    │      lemmas.
    │
    ├── R03__Carryless_Pairing_Examples.v
    │
    │      Concrete realizations and computational examples, including a greedy
    │      Zeckendorf construction and `vm_compute` evaluations.
    │
    └── appendix
           ├── Carryless_Pairing.ml
           │
           │      Extracted OCaml implementation of the verified “Carryless
           │      pairing construction.
           │
           ├── Carryless_Pairing.mli
           │
           │      Generated OCaml interface exposing the extracted types and
           │      functions.
           │
           ├── assumptions.log
           │
           │      Output of `Print Assumptions` for the principal correctness
           │      theorems.
           │
           └── v.context.txt
           
                  Snapshot of the main `.v` sources at extraction
                  time, included for traceability.
